Storing of task description gets pushed by 1 spacing

commitResults.messageTitle: Add DateTimeParser for Wanya to understand date and time
commitResults.messageBody:
DateTimeParser enable Wanya to recognise String of format
"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm" as dates and time respectively.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add exceptions and test for DateTimeParser
commitResults.messageBody:
Add checks to ensure program will not crash if date is not provided
or format of date is invalid. Remind users the correct format
required to add deadlines and events.

Conduct automated text-ui testing for regression testing.
Made some unecessary changes to master branch to be 1 commit ahead.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug of missing details from Wanya file
commitResults.messageBody:
Reason: I should have changed the file name from Duke to Wanya
from the master branch before even creating the new branches, which
led to the changes made in the Level-8 branch to not be reflected in
the master Branch.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug of date time format not displayed properly
commitResults.messageBody:
Initially, the date time format shown on the deadline and event
are in the DateTime format rather than my intended format. I have
missed out the function call when converting toString method.
Code is working as intended and conducted text-UI test.

Create 4 new classes
- Ui to deal with interaction with users
- Parser to make sense of the command user inputs
- TaskList to contain task list and handle tasks operations
- Storage to load and save task list

- Divide classes into packages
- Reformat tasks string format in Storage
